d 'PRAISK': module to perform Iterated Prais-Winsten regression with AR(k) errors
d
d      praisk fits a linear regression model with autoregressive
d errors AR(k) using the iterated Prais-Winsten (generalized least 
d   squares) estimator. For AR(k>1), praisk follows the methods
d described in Vougas (2021). The transformation uses exact   
d initialization of the first k observations following Galbraith
d and Galbraith (1974) and Hamilton (1994). AR(k) parameters are   
d estimated by solving the pooled Yule-Walker cross-product system
d jointly across all panels and segments, matching the behavior   
d of official prais.	After estimation, praisk displays a table
d of residual autocorrelations at lags 1 through k.  The
d untransformed row shows    autocorrelations of the OLS residuals
d (before AR filtering) and the transformed row shows
d autocorrelations of the AR(k)    innovation residuals (after
d filtering).  A successful transformation is indicated by
d transformed autocorrelations close to    zero. For panel data,
d autocorrelations are computed using Stata's lag operator, which
d restricts all pairs to within-panel	 consecutive observations,
d matching the approach used by prais for the Durbin-Watson
d statistic. 
d
d KW: autoregressive errors
d KW: AR(p)
d KW: time series
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260619
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
f praisk.ado
f praisk_p.ado
f praisk.sthlp
f praisk_methods.pdf
